WEBVTT

00:00.329 --> 00:01.649
AMY: Previously on "Heartland:"

00:01.689 --> 00:03.654
TY: It's injured,
look at all that blood.

00:04.200 --> 00:06.067
Her leg's gone through the bridge.

00:06.168 --> 00:07.802
I'm dating again.

00:07.903 --> 00:10.871
Oh... wow.

00:10.906 --> 00:13.575
Dean Woodley. Not impressed.

00:13.676 --> 00:15.276
<i>He wants to gift Bandit to his daughter</i>

00:15.378 --> 00:16.878
<i>for her birthday.</i>

00:16.979 --> 00:18.980
I'm gonna propose to Casey.

00:19.081 --> 00:20.949
I'm-I'm gonna ask her to marry me.

00:21.050 --> 00:22.350
Dad!

00:24.053 --> 00:26.688
Wow,
I've never seen Bandit take any interest

00:26.789 --> 00:28.256
in another horse before.

00:28.357 --> 00:30.825
I want us to be partners!
I want us to work together.

00:30.926 --> 00:32.127
Like we dreamed about.

00:32.228 --> 00:34.396
- You sold Big River?
- Today.

00:38.601 --> 00:39.701
(HOOVES THUD)

00:40.469 --> 00:42.370
(MARE SNORTS)

00:43.739 --> 00:45.940
(FOAL WHINNIES)

00:49.612 --> 00:51.579
(HOOVES THUD)

00:53.549 --> 00:55.350
(HOOVES CLOMP)

00:57.019 --> 00:59.120
AMY: Good boy, Bandit.

00:59.221 --> 01:01.389
(BANDIT NICKERS)

01:03.092 --> 01:04.358
DEAN: He's looking good, Amy!

01:04.459 --> 01:06.461
He's totally fine being ridden now.

01:06.562 --> 01:07.796
I had Ty ride him,

01:07.897 --> 01:09.697
Georgie took him on a trail.

01:09.799 --> 01:12.033
Your daughter is gonna love him.

01:12.134 --> 01:13.601
What a change!

01:13.702 --> 01:15.336
And look at him with other horses.

01:15.438 --> 01:17.505
Yeah, he's doing really great.

01:17.606 --> 01:19.140
Aren't you, Bandit?

01:19.241 --> 01:20.608
You wanna go see your friends?

01:20.709 --> 01:23.178
Unbelievable, you did it!
I mean, that is fantastic.

01:23.279 --> 01:25.547
Well, it wasn't just me.

01:25.648 --> 01:28.183
Ty and I are working with
this wild mare and her foal

01:28.284 --> 01:31.419
that we rescued,
and Bandit totally bonded with the mare.

01:31.520 --> 01:33.188
She was a big help in his recovery.

01:33.289 --> 01:36.057
So, you two are working together now?

01:36.158 --> 01:39.494
- We are.
- Well, that's interesting.

01:39.595 --> 01:41.830
A vet and a horse
whisperer joining forces.

01:41.931 --> 01:43.965
That's a one-stop shop. (LAUGHS)

01:44.066 --> 01:46.034
That's good to know.

01:46.135 --> 01:47.969
(DOOR LATCH CLICKS)

01:49.839 --> 01:52.440
Here's my card.

01:52.541 --> 01:54.175
I'm gonna keep in touch.

01:54.276 --> 01:56.077
I have a whole stable
full of my own horses,

01:56.178 --> 01:58.346
I board polo ponies,
I have a ton of contacts,

01:58.447 --> 02:01.316
I can make sure they all
know about your enterprise.

02:01.417 --> 02:03.451
- All right.
- Do you have a card?

02:03.552 --> 02:05.720
Um, not yet.

02:05.821 --> 02:07.922
- We're um...
- No worries.

02:08.023 --> 02:09.657
I've got your contact info.

02:09.758 --> 02:10.959
- Okay.
- All the best.

02:11.060 --> 02:12.861
- Thanks, Dean.
- Thank you.

02:12.962 --> 02:15.096
Thank you, you did it!

02:15.197 --> 02:17.632
(TY AND AMY CHUCKLE)

02:19.668 --> 02:20.802
(TRUCK ENGINE TURNS OVER)

02:20.903 --> 02:23.438
- AMY AND TY: We need a card.
- GEORGIE: Guys!

02:23.539 --> 02:25.073
They're not there! The mare and foal.

02:25.174 --> 02:27.575
- I can't find them anywhere.
- Oh no, not again.

02:32.214 --> 02:34.249
(GATE CLANGS)

02:35.551 --> 02:37.051
(HORSES SNORT)

02:38.187 --> 02:40.388
(HOOVES THUD)

02:40.489 --> 02:41.923
Thanks, Georgie.

02:42.925 --> 02:45.460
(SIGHS)

02:45.561 --> 02:47.595
(HOOVES THUD)

02:53.168 --> 02:55.069
(HORSES SNORT)

02:57.806 --> 02:59.274
(BIRDS CHIRP)

03:02.611 --> 03:03.945
(HORSES PANT)

03:06.515 --> 03:09.717
TY: This is the third
time they've gotten out.

03:09.818 --> 03:11.619
(SPARTAN BLOWS NOISILY)

03:11.720 --> 03:13.922
That mare is like Houdini.

03:14.023 --> 03:16.090
A total escape artist.

03:17.860 --> 03:18.960
(HORSES SNORT)

03:20.496 --> 03:22.564
- (DISTANT SHRILL WHINNY)
- Ty!

03:25.200 --> 03:27.201
(FOAL WHINNIES AGITATEDLY)

03:28.203 --> 03:31.439
(WEAK WHINNY, SNORTS)

03:33.146 --> 03:38.068
S12E02
Hearts Run Free

03:39.194 --> 03:45.816
sync and corrected by ninh
www.addic7ed.com

03:47.990 --> 03:50.425
♪ And at the break of day

03:50.526 --> 03:53.761
♪ You sank into your dream

03:55.097 --> 03:57.231
♪ You dreamer

03:57.333 --> 03:59.434
♪ Oh oh oh oh

03:59.535 --> 04:01.135
♪ You dreamer

04:03.739 --> 04:07.575
♪ You dreamer

04:13.816 --> 04:15.650
- (GASPS)
- Oh...

04:15.751 --> 04:18.052
Whoa, whoa.

04:18.153 --> 04:19.988
- Easy.
- Easy, girl.

04:20.089 --> 04:21.856
It doesn't matter what
size field I put them in,

04:21.957 --> 04:24.058
they're gonna try to escape.

04:24.159 --> 04:25.193
(MARE SNORTS) You're okay.

04:25.294 --> 04:27.729
Oh! Oh! Whoa, whoa. (MARE WHINNIES)

04:27.830 --> 04:30.531
Well, they're wild horses.
That's what they do.

04:30.633 --> 04:32.467
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

04:32.568 --> 04:35.570
(MARE SNORTS, TY GRUNTS WITH EFFORT)

04:35.671 --> 04:38.139
She could've seriously injured herself,
Amy.

04:38.240 --> 04:40.375
I know.

04:41.677 --> 04:43.011
(FOAL NICKERS)

04:43.112 --> 04:45.079
- (MARE WHINNIES)
- Whoa, whoa.

04:45.180 --> 04:48.182
They can't stay at Heartland.

04:48.283 --> 04:49.917
Whoa...

04:52.154 --> 04:54.389
(MARE AND FOAL GRUNT SOFTLY)

04:54.490 --> 04:56.190
You can get up.

04:56.291 --> 04:58.626
(MARE SNORTS)

04:58.727 --> 05:00.728
(WHINNIES)

05:02.197 --> 05:04.065
(SNORTS)

05:06.635 --> 05:08.503
(SNORTING)

05:08.604 --> 05:10.772
(BIRDS CHIRP)

05:10.873 --> 05:13.107
So when did you hear from her?

05:13.208 --> 05:14.742
A couple of days ago, or so.

05:14.843 --> 05:17.278
But we are talking,
and she really does want me to come

05:17.379 --> 05:18.913
as soon as possible.

05:19.014 --> 05:22.050
So Dear Aunt Evelyn
wants you to trek halfway

05:22.151 --> 05:25.219
across the world to Istanbul
to be her traveling buddy?

05:25.320 --> 05:27.221
(CHUCKLES)

05:27.322 --> 05:29.223
(SIGHS) Well,
what about our own getaway?

05:29.324 --> 05:31.292
We were heading up to
Emerald Lake for a few days.

05:31.393 --> 05:33.661
Yes, I know, and you know
how excited I was about that.

05:33.762 --> 05:35.997
And that's why I haven't talked
to you about this before now.

05:36.098 --> 05:38.666
But... I thought it was gonna blow over,

05:38.767 --> 05:40.201
I guess she's having some troubles

05:40.302 --> 05:41.769
with her new boyfriend.

05:41.870 --> 05:43.604
Shocking.

05:43.706 --> 05:45.206
And she's alone, and needs me,

05:45.307 --> 05:46.607
and I feel badly!

05:46.709 --> 05:48.876
Isn't she always bragging
about how she likes

05:48.977 --> 05:51.446
to travel alone?

05:51.547 --> 05:56.038
Lis,
you know I made peace with your aunt,

05:56.452 --> 05:58.086
but you don't need to
be at her beck and call.

05:58.187 --> 06:01.122
I mean, she's a grown woman.

06:01.223 --> 06:03.891
Okay, so, so...

06:03.992 --> 06:06.127
I'll say no?

06:08.263 --> 06:10.798
(RADIO PLAYS ROCK SONG)

06:10.899 --> 06:12.900
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

06:15.204 --> 06:17.605
Ugh, Lou. Stop calling!

06:18.674 --> 06:20.675
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

06:22.911 --> 06:25.113
(TRUCK RUMBLES)

06:25.214 --> 06:28.049
(TIRES CRUNCH ON GRAVEL)

06:29.952 --> 06:32.019
Dad! Where are you?

06:32.121 --> 06:34.055
How did it go with Casey?

06:34.156 --> 06:36.390
Just call me back and let
me know what happened,

06:36.492 --> 06:38.593
because you're making me crazy!

06:39.595 --> 06:41.796
And by the way,
did you know about Mitch?

06:41.897 --> 06:43.865
That he's seeing someone?!

06:43.966 --> 06:46.067
Hey, where's Amy?

06:46.168 --> 06:48.002
I thought you guys had
a coaching session.

06:48.103 --> 06:50.738
The mare and foal escaped. Again.

06:50.839 --> 06:53.207
She and Ty are out looking for them.

06:53.308 --> 06:55.209
Tell me I'm not a horrible person.

06:55.310 --> 06:57.278
You're not a horrible person.

06:57.379 --> 06:58.846
Why do I need to say that?

06:58.947 --> 06:59.947
There's this coach I heard about,

07:00.048 --> 07:02.316
Kim Price, and she's...

07:02.417 --> 07:04.051
amazing, like, so amazing.

07:04.153 --> 07:06.554
And she has an opening right now, but...

07:06.655 --> 07:08.022
if I don't go for it right away,

07:08.123 --> 07:09.557
then I'll miss out.

07:09.658 --> 07:11.826
You're thinking about switching coaches?

07:11.927 --> 07:14.562
See? I told you, I'm a horrible person.

07:14.663 --> 07:16.164
I've never imagined switching,

07:16.265 --> 07:18.332
but I just think that Amy feels guilty

07:18.433 --> 07:19.634
about not having enough time for me,

07:19.735 --> 07:22.203
and I don't wanna be a burden.

07:22.304 --> 07:24.071
(SIGHS) This coach never has openings,

07:24.173 --> 07:26.073
so I'm thinking maybe it's a sign.

07:26.175 --> 07:28.109
I think I should at
least give it a shot.

07:28.210 --> 07:30.044
And she probably won't even accept me,

07:30.145 --> 07:31.779
She only coaches top riders.

07:31.880 --> 07:34.315
You are a top rider, Georgie.

07:34.416 --> 07:36.551
(HOOVES THUD)

07:36.652 --> 07:38.586
Hey, I'm so sorry I took so long.

07:38.687 --> 07:39.887
Did you find them?

07:39.988 --> 07:41.322
Yeah, but Ty's still with the mare.

07:41.423 --> 07:44.025
She got into some barbed wire.

07:44.126 --> 07:45.660
If it's okay,
I'm just gonna run and check

07:45.761 --> 07:47.361
if Grandpa's good with Lyndy.

07:47.462 --> 07:50.131
And I'll be right back as soon as I can,
I promise.

07:53.368 --> 07:55.102
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

07:55.204 --> 07:57.104
AMY: I don't know what to do, Grandpa.

07:57.206 --> 07:59.073
I mean, they're wild,
they're meant to be free,

07:59.174 --> 08:01.008
I don't wanna tame them.

08:01.109 --> 08:04.011
Well, it sounds to me like
they need to be adopted

08:04.112 --> 08:05.479
by another herd.

08:05.581 --> 08:07.148
That would be ideal.

08:07.249 --> 08:09.016
What about those wildies
up at Pike River?

08:09.117 --> 08:11.719
I'm pretty sure Will
still looks in on them.

08:11.820 --> 08:14.555
That's the perfect home for them,
Grandpa.

08:14.656 --> 08:16.891
Well, I'll give him a call.

08:16.992 --> 08:19.293
And see what he has to
say about the situation.

08:19.394 --> 08:20.761
Thanks.

08:20.863 --> 08:24.031
I've been meaning to get a
hold of my old friend anyway.

08:24.132 --> 08:25.833
If you're serious about
this coaching decision,

08:25.934 --> 08:28.436
then you need to tell
Amy sooner than later.

08:28.537 --> 08:31.572
I mean, who knows,
maybe she's gonna be relieved.

08:31.673 --> 08:33.441
Just make sure that you're clear

08:33.542 --> 08:35.376
that it's not because she's a bad coach.

08:35.477 --> 08:37.912
No, it's not about that.

08:40.816 --> 08:43.351
Okay, well, I'll let you guys get to it.

08:44.686 --> 08:46.621
What's up?

08:46.722 --> 08:48.155
(SIGHS)

08:49.858 --> 08:51.926
Look Georgie, I know that I
haven't been able to give you

08:52.027 --> 08:54.262
the training time that you need,
and for that, I'm sorry.

08:54.363 --> 08:57.064
No! It's not that! Not at all!

08:57.165 --> 09:00.034
You've been amazing,
you haven't done anything wrong.

09:00.135 --> 09:02.970
I'm gonna choose to believe that.

09:03.071 --> 09:06.941
And Georgie, I've seen this Kim Price.

09:07.042 --> 09:09.777
She is as amazing as everyone says.

09:09.878 --> 09:12.880
So maybe this is the next
logical step for you to take.

09:12.981 --> 09:14.982
Because in the end,
I just want what's best for you.

09:15.083 --> 09:16.817
You're what's best.

09:16.919 --> 09:18.452
You are, I mean that.

09:19.454 --> 09:21.155
And if this trainer doesn't take me...

09:21.256 --> 09:23.891
She's gonna take you, she will.

09:25.127 --> 09:26.494
(SIGHS)

09:30.265 --> 09:33.467
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

09:36.772 --> 09:38.906
(BIRDS CHIRP)

09:39.007 --> 09:42.543
AMY: So we may have a solution
for the mare and her foal.

09:42.644 --> 09:44.912
- Oh yeah?
- Yeah, Grandpa talked to Will.

09:45.013 --> 09:47.048
And he thinks that it's a good
idea to try and mix them in

09:47.149 --> 09:49.150
with his wild herd.

09:49.251 --> 09:51.552
Oh. Are you sure that's a good idea,
though?

09:51.653 --> 09:53.988
I mean,
herds have a pretty crazy hierarchy.

09:54.089 --> 09:56.390
I'm sure they got kicked
out of the last one.

09:56.491 --> 09:58.459
Yeah, it can work.

09:58.560 --> 10:00.861
My mom actually wrote a lot
about it in her journals.

10:00.963 --> 10:02.697
I was thinking we could give it a try.

10:02.798 --> 10:04.999
Yeah, I'd be down with that.

10:05.100 --> 10:06.367
When does he want us to drive out?

10:06.468 --> 10:09.203
Whenever works for us.
He said he'd be happy to help.

10:09.304 --> 10:10.871
Okay, well,
I'm thinking sooner rather than later,

10:10.973 --> 10:13.007
before that mare attempts
another prison break.

10:13.108 --> 10:14.709
Yeah...

10:15.811 --> 10:17.678
Hey, Amy.

10:19.514 --> 10:21.816
You okay?

10:21.917 --> 10:24.251
Georgie fired me as her coach.

10:24.353 --> 10:26.721
(LAUGHS) She fired you?

10:26.822 --> 10:28.856
Well, I haven't had the
time to spend with her.

10:28.957 --> 10:30.891
And she's absolutely right
to find someone else,

10:30.993 --> 10:33.995
but it still kinda hurts.

10:37.399 --> 10:38.866
Hey.

10:38.967 --> 10:40.701
Let's get Lou to babysit
Lyndy for a few days,

10:40.802 --> 10:42.636
And you and I will go to Pike River.

10:42.738 --> 10:44.305
We'll do this thing together.

10:44.406 --> 10:46.774
What do you say?

10:46.875 --> 10:49.910
Maybe we could stay in our cabin.

10:50.012 --> 10:52.380
You remember that? I do remember that.

10:52.481 --> 10:54.248
That was the wedding
that never happened.

10:54.349 --> 10:56.384
Yes, and thank goodness we didn't elope.

10:56.485 --> 10:57.985
Can you imagine Lou?

10:58.086 --> 10:59.620
(LAUGHS)

11:01.023 --> 11:02.757
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

11:04.326 --> 11:07.228
(BAG AND BOX CLATTER)

11:11.066 --> 11:12.299
JACK: Where did you disappear to?

11:12.401 --> 11:14.468
I've been trying to get in
touch with you for a few days,

11:14.569 --> 11:18.305
and what are you doing
with all that stuff?!

11:18.407 --> 11:19.640
I'm moving in.

11:19.741 --> 11:21.275
Moving in where?

11:21.376 --> 11:22.777
Here.

11:22.878 --> 11:25.179
To Heartland.

11:29.584 --> 11:32.319
<i>(SCREEN DOOR BANGS) Hey, Lisa!</i>

11:37.281 --> 11:40.016
<i>- Hey.
- Wow, what is going on here?</i>

11:40.117 --> 11:41.951
- Ask him.
- I sold Big River.

11:42.052 --> 11:43.519
I told you, that's what's going on.

11:43.620 --> 11:45.621
Selling that ranch was your decision,

11:45.723 --> 11:48.424
not mine, so you can't just...

11:48.525 --> 11:50.760
- we need to talk about this.
- Oh, we'll talk about it.

11:50.861 --> 11:52.895
But could we eat first, please?

11:52.996 --> 11:55.298
Thank you, everybody, come on.

11:55.399 --> 11:57.166
- Dad!
- I got your voice-mail.

11:57.267 --> 11:58.868
I want to know what's going on with you!

11:58.969 --> 12:00.636
- What?!
- What happened with Casey?

12:00.738 --> 12:02.338
I can't say anything
in front of the others!

12:02.439 --> 12:03.973
Oh, I'm surprised you
haven't spilled the beans

12:04.074 --> 12:05.675
- to everybody already.
- Dad,

12:05.776 --> 12:07.443
I said I wouldn't say anything,
and I haven't,

12:07.544 --> 12:09.445
but it just about killed me.

12:09.546 --> 12:11.881
Okay, now tell me what happened! Dad!

12:11.982 --> 12:13.449
Never mind that.

12:13.550 --> 12:15.785
Have you made a decision about Maggie's,
and Nicole yet?

12:15.886 --> 12:17.120
No, and don't say anything.

12:17.221 --> 12:19.055
I haven't told anyone about that,
either.

12:19.156 --> 12:20.857
So many secrets, Lou.

12:20.958 --> 12:22.325
Your head must be ready to explode.

12:22.426 --> 12:24.193
(SCOFFS)

12:26.663 --> 12:28.331
AMY: Okay,
but what I don't understand is,

12:28.432 --> 12:30.466
why did you have to move
out of Big River so fast?

12:30.567 --> 12:32.468
There's a lot of things
I don't understand.

12:32.569 --> 12:35.338
My buyer wanted a quick close
and I was fine with that.

12:35.439 --> 12:37.607
Yeah well, you know what?
I'm not fine with it.

12:37.708 --> 12:40.076
What makes you think you
can just move in here?!

12:40.177 --> 12:42.612
Relax Jack, it's temporary.

12:42.713 --> 12:45.915
(CELL PHONE CHIMES) Oh, shoot. Sorry.

12:46.016 --> 12:48.351
That's rude,
I have to actually take this, excuse me.

12:49.653 --> 12:51.788
TY: Hm.
We should probably get going too,

12:51.889 --> 12:53.456
I'd love to stay for some cherry pie,

12:53.557 --> 12:55.057
- but we gotta get goin'.
- Yeah.

12:55.159 --> 12:56.926
- Where you going?
- Pike River.

12:57.027 --> 12:58.494
We're leaving first
thing in the morning.

12:58.595 --> 13:00.630
Well,
given the new living circumstances,

13:00.731 --> 13:02.632
I'll move into the loft so
I can take care of Lyndy.

13:02.733 --> 13:04.500
- Okay.
- Great, I'll take your room.

13:04.601 --> 13:07.403
'Cause the bed in Amy's old
room is way too small, so...

13:07.504 --> 13:08.971
that's settled.

13:09.072 --> 13:10.840
I think I'll just hit the sack.

13:15.345 --> 13:17.146
<i>(COYOTES HOWL)</i>

13:17.247 --> 13:18.948
JACK: Do you believe that guy?!

13:19.049 --> 13:20.516
I still can't believe it!

13:20.617 --> 13:23.152
Hey? Tim, moving in here like that,

13:23.253 --> 13:25.721
Who does he think he is?

13:25.823 --> 13:27.824
So that call during
dinner was from Evelyn,

13:27.925 --> 13:30.326
and uh,
it turns out that she is very sick.

13:30.427 --> 13:32.195
And that's why she wants me to come.

13:32.296 --> 13:33.930
- She's sick?
- Yes.

13:34.031 --> 13:36.499
She's manipulating you.

13:36.600 --> 13:38.734
She's not manipulating me Jack,
she's ill!

13:38.836 --> 13:41.103
No, she says she's ill.

13:41.205 --> 13:42.438
Evelyn is Evelyn.

13:42.539 --> 13:44.173
She's just goin' back to her old ways.

13:44.274 --> 13:47.143
You can't change a leopard's spots.

13:47.244 --> 13:49.612
Well, I'm going to take her at her word.

13:49.713 --> 13:51.647
Okay?

13:53.283 --> 13:55.151
It's because Tim's moving in.

13:55.252 --> 13:57.019
That's why you suddenly wanna go!

13:57.120 --> 13:58.821
Hey, I don't blame you.

13:58.922 --> 14:00.790
I get it,
I'll just tell him he can't move in,

14:00.891 --> 14:02.225
and that'll be the end of it.

14:02.326 --> 14:04.660
Actually,
Tim has nothing to do with this.

14:04.761 --> 14:06.162
I-that whole thing, I...

14:06.263 --> 14:08.297
it does not factor in
to my decision at all.

14:08.398 --> 14:09.966
(KEYS TAP)

14:10.067 --> 14:12.368
So you already made the decision, then?

14:12.469 --> 14:14.103
Yes, I think I should go!

14:14.204 --> 14:17.773
So I-no I, yes, I have,
I've made my decision.

14:18.809 --> 14:21.110
Fine, go.

14:21.211 --> 14:22.678
And I'm going too.

14:24.314 --> 14:26.582
To Istanbul? Don't be silly!

14:26.683 --> 14:28.251
You don't wanna go to Istanbul!

14:28.352 --> 14:31.721
You got that right,
I'm going to Pike River with Amy and Ty.

14:31.822 --> 14:34.056
And I'm telling him he
better have alternate plans

14:34.157 --> 14:35.925
by the time I get back.

14:39.897 --> 14:41.564
(TIGHT INHALE)

14:41.665 --> 14:43.432
(BELL DINGS)

14:45.002 --> 14:46.769
(CLOTHES RUSTLING IN THE WIND)

14:50.007 --> 14:52.074
You be a good girl for Mom, okay?

14:52.175 --> 14:53.476
You're sure you're gonna
be all right with her?

14:53.577 --> 14:55.611
Of course, we're gonna have so much fun!

14:55.712 --> 14:57.280
- Aren't we?
- Mommy.

14:57.381 --> 14:58.748
Yeah, you guys have fun too, okay?

14:58.849 --> 15:01.150
- I hope it all goes well.
- Okay.

15:03.520 --> 15:05.187
I'm coming with you.

15:05.289 --> 15:06.589
Why?

15:06.690 --> 15:09.191
Well, you'll need a hand
with the horses, and...

15:09.293 --> 15:11.160
Oh Jack, we're fine, really.

15:11.261 --> 15:13.930
No, no, it's settled.

15:14.031 --> 15:16.232
- (LYNDY COOS)
- Okay.

15:16.333 --> 15:18.067
(LAUGHS WRYLY)

15:19.202 --> 15:21.737
- (TOASTER POPS)
- Oh! That's me.

15:22.739 --> 15:24.774
- Whoop! Ah! Ow! Ow! Ow!
- So they're off?

15:24.875 --> 15:26.776
LOU: Yes,
I'm not sure they were totally thrilled

15:26.877 --> 15:30.646
about Grandpa going along,
but Amy and Ty are off.

15:30.747 --> 15:33.115
Oh hey,
so there's a couple of voice messages

15:33.216 --> 15:35.918
on the landline for you two,
Nicole called again.

15:36.019 --> 15:38.087
And Kim Price, for you.

15:38.188 --> 15:39.789
- Kim Price? Really?
- Yeah. Yeah.

15:39.890 --> 15:41.424
Said she can meet you today for lunch.

15:41.525 --> 15:43.092
There you go, she's interested.

15:43.193 --> 15:45.227
- Well, you have to go with me!
- Uh...

15:45.329 --> 15:46.662
I'll babysit, that's fine.

15:46.763 --> 15:50.232
TIM: I can babysit. I live here now.

15:50.334 --> 15:52.335
I wanna be useful, I'll babysit.

15:52.436 --> 15:54.170
I need to call Kim back!

15:56.006 --> 15:58.574
Hm. You gonna call Nicole?

15:58.675 --> 16:00.543
- No.
- Why?

16:00.644 --> 16:02.078
It's complicated, okay?

16:02.179 --> 16:04.280
Um, Auntie Lou is gonna be right back,

16:04.381 --> 16:05.815
you go with Grandpa.

16:05.916 --> 16:08.884
Does that complication have
something to do with Mitch?

16:08.986 --> 16:10.486
Okay, I have to ask.

16:10.587 --> 16:13.422
Did you know that he was seeing someone?

16:13.523 --> 16:15.291
Seeing someone?

16:15.392 --> 16:16.792
He is?

16:16.893 --> 16:18.461
(AGGRAVATED EXHALE)

16:19.529 --> 16:21.030
(DEEP INHALE)

16:21.131 --> 16:22.999
(MESSAGE CHIMES)

16:23.100 --> 16:24.700
(DISHES CLINK, MUSIC PLAYS)

16:24.801 --> 16:27.036
Are you okay?

16:27.137 --> 16:30.039
This is a terrible idea.
Kim Price is in crazy demand.

16:30.140 --> 16:31.641
I'm sure I'm not good enough.

16:31.742 --> 16:33.943
Kim Price would be lucky
to have you as a client.

16:34.044 --> 16:36.912
Okay, just present your best self.

16:37.014 --> 16:40.116
If you don't believe in you,
nobody else will.

16:40.217 --> 16:41.951
(DOOR BANGS)

16:42.052 --> 16:43.719
Hi, I'm Lou, Georgie's Mom.

16:43.820 --> 16:45.454
Hi, so nice to meet you.

16:45.555 --> 16:48.290
Georgie, hi,
so nice to finally see you in person.

16:48.392 --> 16:50.292
- Please, sit.
- Thanks.

16:51.495 --> 16:52.728
Great you could meet us.

16:52.829 --> 16:54.664
Oh, how I've looked forward to it.

16:54.765 --> 16:56.666
I've been following Georgie's career,
and I must say,

16:56.767 --> 16:59.135
I'm very impressed.

16:59.236 --> 17:00.836
I'd be more than happy to coach you.

17:00.937 --> 17:03.506
And it just so happens,
I have a spot open.

17:03.607 --> 17:05.273
Amazing.

17:05.375 --> 17:07.076
But there is one condition.

17:07.176 --> 17:08.310
Okay.

17:08.412 --> 17:09.845
I'll only coach you if you ride a horse

17:09.945 --> 17:11.747
of my choosing.

17:11.848 --> 17:15.704
Um, no. I can't do that.

17:15.833 --> 17:17.787
Georgie, we should consider...

17:17.887 --> 17:19.555
I've been down that road before.

17:19.656 --> 17:20.856
Phoenix and I are a team.

17:20.957 --> 17:22.625
I can't compete on any other horse.

17:22.726 --> 17:24.393
Now, hold on, just let me explain.

17:24.493 --> 17:26.662
Georgie, I see huge potential in you,

17:26.762 --> 17:28.196
but I believe, having watched playbacks

17:28.298 --> 17:30.266
of many of your show performances,

17:30.367 --> 17:32.635
that Phoenix is holding you back.

17:32.736 --> 17:34.403
I'm absolutely certain that
when you start competing

17:34.504 --> 17:36.372
at a higher level,
you'll find your competition

17:36.473 --> 17:38.207
is much faster.

17:38.308 --> 17:41.043
I'm sorry. Look, I know my horse.

17:41.144 --> 17:42.445
I know he's fast enough.

17:42.546 --> 17:44.613
And I-I can prove it if I have to.

17:46.216 --> 17:47.917
Okay. How?

17:49.086 --> 17:51.087
Well, we could...

17:51.188 --> 17:53.422
set up a course at Heartland.

17:53.523 --> 17:56.258
You could ride it,
and name the time I have to beat.

17:56.359 --> 17:59.462
And if we go clear,
and I beat or meet your time,

18:00.530 --> 18:02.465
will you train Phoenix and I?

18:04.634 --> 18:06.268
(LAUGHS) Okay.

18:07.471 --> 18:09.138
It's a deal.

18:09.239 --> 18:11.040
O-okay!

18:11.141 --> 18:12.908
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

18:13.910 --> 18:16.312
- Nice to meet you, thanks.
- I'll be in touch.

18:20.150 --> 18:23.018
GEORGIE:
That was like an out-of-body experience!

18:23.120 --> 18:25.621
Did I really just say that to Kim Price?

18:25.722 --> 18:27.456
Why? Why did I do that?!

18:27.557 --> 18:29.091
What if I can't make
the course fast enough?

18:29.192 --> 18:30.693
I'm gonna make a
complete fool of myself!

18:30.794 --> 18:31.861
Honey. Georgie.

18:31.962 --> 18:34.697
Just stop panicking,
and start practicing.

18:37.734 --> 18:39.401
I'll wait in the car.

18:41.705 --> 18:43.072
Oh hey, Georgie.

18:46.143 --> 18:47.843
- Hi!
- What's goin' on?

18:47.944 --> 18:49.845
I've been texting you,
you haven't responded.

18:49.946 --> 18:51.514
I just did.

18:51.615 --> 18:54.150
(SIGHS)

18:54.251 --> 18:57.853
Okay well,
up until now you haven't responded.

18:57.954 --> 18:59.655
What's up?

18:59.756 --> 19:01.323
I just, I wanna to make sure you're okay

19:01.424 --> 19:03.092
after what we talked
about the other day.

19:03.193 --> 19:05.528
What we talked a...

19:05.629 --> 19:06.962
yeah, that?

19:07.063 --> 19:09.632
Of course, I'm totally fine.

19:10.967 --> 19:12.968
Okay, good.

19:14.037 --> 19:16.405
There was one thing I was just like,
curious about.

19:16.506 --> 19:18.174
You said you were...

19:18.275 --> 19:20.609
dating again, is that serious,

19:20.710 --> 19:22.945
or is it just casual?

19:23.046 --> 19:26.081
Well, I mean,
we're not putting labels on things.

19:26.183 --> 19:28.217
We're just gonna see how this goes.

19:28.318 --> 19:30.519
See how it goes? That's good.

19:30.620 --> 19:32.021
That's smart.

19:32.122 --> 19:33.823
Yeah, well, I mean, what about you?

19:33.924 --> 19:35.457
Didn't-you said something

19:35.559 --> 19:37.026
about taking a step back from New York?

19:37.127 --> 19:39.128
No, I'm just,
I'm not putting labels on that, either.

19:39.229 --> 19:41.864
I'm just gonna see how it goes.

19:42.866 --> 19:45.034
- So, then we're good?
- Oh yeah, we're good.

19:45.135 --> 19:48.137
We're good, yeah.
If you're happy, I'm happy.

19:49.306 --> 19:51.674
Are you? Happy?

19:54.156 --> 19:55.831
(SIGHS) Yeah, Lou, I'm happy.

19:57.981 --> 20:00.316
That is so good to hear. That's great.

20:00.417 --> 20:04.103
Anyway, Georgie's waiting,
I'll see you later.

20:06.489 --> 20:08.357
(BIRDS CHIRP)

20:09.593 --> 20:11.794
(SINGING, HUMMING SOFTLY)

20:11.895 --> 20:13.162
(HORN HONKS)

20:15.332 --> 20:16.999
Come on right down the road.

20:17.100 --> 20:19.368
(TRUCK RUMBLES)

20:22.272 --> 20:24.139
(TRUCK RUMBLES)

20:24.241 --> 20:27.476
(GATE CLUNKS)

20:27.577 --> 20:29.545
(LAUGHS)

20:29.646 --> 20:30.913
How you doing, Ty?

20:31.014 --> 20:33.015
- Hey!
- Long time!

20:33.116 --> 20:35.951
What can I say? Here, hug me. (CHUCKLES)

20:36.052 --> 20:38.520
No one told me the old man
was gonna get drug up here.

20:38.622 --> 20:40.623
Who you callin' old?

20:40.724 --> 20:41.924
(WILL CHUCKLES)

20:42.025 --> 20:43.158
(HORSES WHINNY)

20:43.260 --> 20:45.594
<i>JACK: Will, you look great.</i>

20:45.695 --> 20:47.496
<i>WILL: Well, of course I do,
what do you expect?</i>

20:47.597 --> 20:49.498
(HOOVES THUD)

20:49.599 --> 20:51.066
<i>JACK: With you,
I never know what to expect.</i>

20:51.167 --> 20:53.402
(HORSES SNORT, WHINNY)
(JACK AND WILL CHUCKLE)

20:53.503 --> 20:56.205
<i>JACK: Well, look at that.</i>

20:56.306 --> 20:58.073
(HOOVES THUD)

20:59.509 --> 21:02.578
Oh Will, they're so beautiful.

21:02.679 --> 21:04.413
(HORSES WHINNY)

21:06.182 --> 21:08.317
<i>Thanks for giving us this chance.</i>

21:08.418 --> 21:09.652
Oh, it's nothing to do with me,

21:09.753 --> 21:11.553
I'm just the guy with the food to them.

21:11.655 --> 21:13.789
- (JACK CHUCKLES)
- No, it's gonna be the herd

21:13.890 --> 21:15.891
that's gonna decide the tale in here.

21:15.992 --> 21:17.459
Well, let's get a look at your wildies.

21:17.560 --> 21:18.994
Okay.

21:19.095 --> 21:21.730
What if we put the mare and
foal on this side of the fence,

21:21.831 --> 21:24.099
So that they can see the herd,
and the herd can see them.

21:24.200 --> 21:26.235
Oh, and they're still protected,
that makes sense.

21:26.336 --> 21:28.203
- Okay, you're the boss.
- Okay.

21:28.305 --> 21:30.806
- All right.
- That's what I say.

21:30.907 --> 21:33.008
Here we go, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

21:33.109 --> 21:34.410
Look out!

21:34.511 --> 21:36.278
(MARE AND FOAL SNORT, WHINNY)

21:36.379 --> 21:38.314
(HORSES SNORT, SNUFFLE)

21:39.582 --> 21:41.183
(HORSE WHINNIES)

21:42.218 --> 21:43.819
(STALLION SNORTS, WHINNIES)

21:43.920 --> 21:46.355
<i>WILL: There he is.</i>

21:46.456 --> 21:48.424
I knew that would happen.

21:48.525 --> 21:50.159
(STALLION WHINNIES)

21:53.897 --> 21:55.464
(AGITATED WHINNY)

22:00.498 --> 22:02.375
You remember this
black stallion, I'm sure.

22:02.501 --> 22:03.668
<i>AMY: Yes, I sure do.</i>

22:03.769 --> 22:06.537
Okay, well, he still rules the roost.

22:06.638 --> 22:09.941
<i>And he's got even more set
in his ways over the years.</i>

22:10.042 --> 22:12.143
<i>He's the one you'll have to win over.</i>

22:12.244 --> 22:13.778
<i>But you've done it before.</i>

22:13.879 --> 22:15.446
Okay, well, we'll take things slow.

22:15.547 --> 22:17.582
We'll introduce the mare
and foal to the herd horses,

22:17.683 --> 22:19.784
just a few at a time.

22:19.885 --> 22:21.986
I'll worry about the stallion later.

22:22.087 --> 22:24.021
Sounds like a plan.

22:24.122 --> 22:26.924
Jack, Will? Can you help us
push a few of them forward?

22:27.025 --> 22:29.460
- Absolutely.
- Sounds good.

22:29.561 --> 22:31.696
(HORSE SNORTS)

22:32.864 --> 22:34.265
(TACK JINGLES)

22:35.467 --> 22:36.701
(DIRT PATTERS)

22:38.870 --> 22:40.304
(HOOVES THUD)

22:40.405 --> 22:42.273
(HORSE PANTS)

22:44.476 --> 22:46.711
(HOOVES THUD)

22:48.814 --> 22:50.481
(HORSE PANTS)

22:53.585 --> 22:55.152
(TACK JINGLES)

22:56.221 --> 22:58.856
(HORSE SNORTS)

22:58.957 --> 23:00.925
(KIM EXHALES)

23:02.494 --> 23:05.062
- 56 seconds.
- I can match that.

23:05.163 --> 23:07.064
You're gonna have to show me
what you've got by tomorrow.

23:07.165 --> 23:08.933
I can't keep the spot
open for very long.

23:09.034 --> 23:10.601
I have another candidate vying for it.

23:10.702 --> 23:14.206
- I hope you understand?
- Of course, I can do that.

23:18.710 --> 23:20.244
(WORRIED EXHALE)

23:21.713 --> 23:23.080
AMY: Once these two get settled,

23:23.181 --> 23:25.283
- then we'll introduce some more.
- TY: Okay.

23:25.384 --> 23:28.419
- (CLUCKS TONGUE) Come on.
- (HORSES WHINNY)

23:28.520 --> 23:30.821
(HORSES NICKER SOFTLY)

23:30.922 --> 23:32.757
(LOUD WHINNY)

23:34.159 --> 23:36.560
Well, they seem pretty
comfortable with these two.

23:36.662 --> 23:38.095
JACK: Uh-oh, watch it!

23:38.196 --> 23:40.831
(STALLION GRUNTS) Whoa, easy, easy.

23:40.932 --> 23:43.234
(SNORTING, HOOF THUDS)

23:43.335 --> 23:44.869
AMY: We've gotta get that stallion

23:44.970 --> 23:46.437
separated from the others.

23:46.538 --> 23:48.205
(AGITATED WHINNYING)

23:48.307 --> 23:49.874
Will, do you have a paddock or something

23:49.975 --> 23:51.175
we could put him in?

23:51.276 --> 23:53.511
Well, we can put him up in there,

23:53.612 --> 23:55.513
but I don't think he's
going to like it very much.

23:55.614 --> 23:58.015
<i>AMY: Okay, let's do it.</i>

23:59.551 --> 24:01.319
(TACK JINGLES)

24:02.421 --> 24:04.655
<i>LOU: Beautiful!</i>

24:04.756 --> 24:06.357
(HOOVES THUD)

24:09.861 --> 24:11.495
(PHOENIX GRUNTS)

24:13.198 --> 24:15.399
(GEORGIE SIGHS)

24:15.500 --> 24:18.469
You're only five seconds
behind Kim's time.

24:18.570 --> 24:20.604
That was good, let's do it again.

24:20.706 --> 24:21.872
(STALLION GRUNTS)

24:21.973 --> 24:24.041
There you go.

24:24.142 --> 24:26.510
(WHINNIES, HOOVES THUD)

24:28.313 --> 24:31.716
AMY: Get the gate, Ty! Ty: Yeah!

24:31.817 --> 24:33.284
Yah!

24:33.385 --> 24:34.885
(AGITATED WHINNIES)

24:34.986 --> 24:36.887
(AGITATED SNORTING)

24:38.590 --> 24:40.257
LOU: Keep your pace up, honey.

24:42.694 --> 24:44.261
(TACK JINGLES)

24:45.530 --> 24:47.398
<i>Atta girl! Yep.</i>

24:48.467 --> 24:50.601
(PHOENIX PANTS)

24:51.737 --> 24:53.304
(HOOVES THUD)

24:53.405 --> 24:55.272
Nice, okay.

24:56.375 --> 24:58.476
You're three seconds over,
you're gettin' there.

24:58.577 --> 24:59.910
(SIGHS)

25:01.847 --> 25:03.614
(HORSE WHINNIES)

25:05.050 --> 25:06.851
(HOOVES CLOMP)

25:07.919 --> 25:09.453
All right, that's the last two.

25:09.554 --> 25:11.622
<i>Ty: Okay.</i>

25:11.723 --> 25:14.291
Let's try this again.

25:14.393 --> 25:16.494
(GATE CREAKS)

25:16.595 --> 25:18.529
(STALLION WHINNIES)

25:19.564 --> 25:21.132
(AGITATED WHINNIES)

25:21.233 --> 25:23.734
(LOW SNORTS)

25:23.835 --> 25:25.503
Whoa...

25:25.604 --> 25:27.171
This isn't going to work.

25:27.272 --> 25:29.306
Let's get him back in.

25:30.575 --> 25:32.643
Whoa.

25:32.744 --> 25:34.278
(STALLION SQUEALS)

25:34.379 --> 25:35.780
Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh!

25:35.881 --> 25:37.314
(WHISTLES) Hup!

25:37.416 --> 25:39.316
(GATE CREAKS)

25:40.452 --> 25:42.553
(STALLION WHINNIES)

25:44.423 --> 25:46.223
(HOOVES THUD)

25:46.324 --> 25:50.027
Come on, boy, don't you remember me?

25:50.128 --> 25:51.662
(SNORTS)

25:52.764 --> 25:54.231
(GRUNTS)

25:54.332 --> 25:56.834
(SIGHS)

25:56.935 --> 25:58.002
Come on.

25:58.103 --> 26:00.905
<i>LOU: Okay, let's keep the pace up.</i>

26:01.006 --> 26:02.406
- Oh!
- Beautiful!

26:04.109 --> 26:07.445
Georgie, cut on the inside on this one!

26:07.546 --> 26:10.047
There you go, nice!

26:10.148 --> 26:12.116
(HOOVES THUD)

26:13.985 --> 26:15.252
<i>Oh... here, too!</i>

26:15.353 --> 26:17.321
<i>Cut along the inside!</i>

26:17.422 --> 26:19.356
(HOOVES THUD)

26:21.359 --> 26:23.894
- How was that?
- That was amazing.

26:23.995 --> 26:26.263
But you're still about
two seconds too slow.

26:26.364 --> 26:28.232
(SIGHS) Are you kidding me?!

26:28.333 --> 26:30.501
How am I ever gonna get this?
Kim comes tomorrow!

26:30.602 --> 26:33.704
Come on, you're gonna get there,
we can do this.

26:33.805 --> 26:35.172
(SIGHS)

26:35.273 --> 26:37.508
(STRUMS A TUNE ON THE GUITAR)

26:40.979 --> 26:42.379
Hey.

26:43.782 --> 26:45.683
Sounding good.

26:45.784 --> 26:48.853
(CHUCKLES) Here you go. Thanks.

26:48.954 --> 26:50.521
- Ah...
- Cheers.

26:51.590 --> 26:54.925
- Is this lemonade?
- Yeah, I'm off the booze, eh?

26:55.026 --> 26:57.495
Apparently, it made me cranky.

26:57.596 --> 26:59.230
Well, you know, I have noticed

26:59.331 --> 27:02.299
that my normally morose
and cynical friend

27:02.400 --> 27:05.603
has been unusually upbeat.

27:05.871 --> 27:07.304
That's 'cause it's your fault.

27:07.405 --> 27:09.240
It's my fault? How's that my fault?

27:09.341 --> 27:11.642
You remember the last
time we saw each other?

27:11.743 --> 27:14.645
Of course, you inducted me
into the Cowboy Hall of Fame.

27:14.746 --> 27:16.247
I'll never forget that.

27:16.348 --> 27:19.416
And then, the next day,
when I was leaving,

27:19.518 --> 27:21.552
you handed me a piece of advice.

27:21.653 --> 27:23.220
You remember what you said?

27:23.321 --> 27:26.190
You said I should make amends with my...

27:26.291 --> 27:27.658
with my ex.

27:27.759 --> 27:30.323
Well sir, I did just that.

27:30.428 --> 27:31.862
No kidding.

27:31.963 --> 27:33.330
I mean, it didn't happen overnight,

27:33.431 --> 27:35.399
oh my God.

27:35.500 --> 27:37.668
I mean,
my lady and I have smoothed things over.

27:37.769 --> 27:40.571
We have managed to
re-establish a friendship.

27:40.672 --> 27:43.741
A really rock-solid friendship.

27:43.842 --> 27:45.976
Well, that is terrific, Will.

27:46.077 --> 27:48.312
And it obviously agrees with you.

27:48.413 --> 27:50.414
Well, thanks,
she has to kinda clean me up

27:50.515 --> 27:54.251
a little bit, sure, yeah. Yeah, yeah.

27:54.352 --> 27:56.887
And how's uh, your lovely wife, Lisa?

27:56.988 --> 27:58.289
What's goin' on?

27:58.390 --> 28:00.624
Well, Lisa and I, we're good.

28:00.725 --> 28:02.493
- That's excellent.
- Yeah.

28:02.594 --> 28:03.928
Yeah, we're good.

28:04.029 --> 28:05.496
We've hit a few rough
spots here and there.

28:05.597 --> 28:07.665
Some growing pains, you know.

28:07.766 --> 28:10.501
I think she's going away soon, too,

28:10.602 --> 28:14.004
Traveling with her Aunt Evelyn.

28:14.105 --> 28:17.808
Oh, it sounds to me like
this aunt isn't exactly

28:17.909 --> 28:19.443
your favourite person.

28:19.544 --> 28:21.845
Ah, she's all right.

28:21.947 --> 28:24.648
But I just think that, you know,

28:24.749 --> 28:27.051
Lisa gets manipulated by her.

28:27.152 --> 28:31.622
And I just wish that she
could say no to her, and...

28:31.723 --> 28:32.957
You're not gonna go turning

28:33.058 --> 28:34.692
into some kind of morose househusband,

28:34.793 --> 28:35.960
or something here, are you?

28:36.061 --> 28:37.728
'Cause trust me on this,
it's not attractive.

28:37.829 --> 28:39.496
I can promise you that.

28:40.498 --> 28:41.932
You're a cowboy, Jack.

28:42.033 --> 28:44.468
You always have been,
you're always gonna be.

28:44.569 --> 28:46.170
And Lisa loves you for that.

28:46.271 --> 28:49.173
So don't go changing into someone else.

28:49.274 --> 28:50.708
Especially when that someone else sounds

28:50.809 --> 28:52.843
an awful lot like the
idiot I used to be.

28:52.944 --> 28:54.511
Yeah, you wish.

28:54.613 --> 28:56.480
No, I'm serious.

28:56.581 --> 28:57.982
Now, quit feeling sorry for yourself.

28:58.083 --> 29:00.284
If Lisa here,
if she wants to go on this trip,

29:00.385 --> 29:02.620
what you gotta do is just let her.

29:02.721 --> 29:05.155
And just relax.
Have you still got that fishing cabin?

29:05.256 --> 29:06.423
Yeah, yeah, I do.

29:06.524 --> 29:07.958
Well, that's what you do, then.

29:08.059 --> 29:09.727
You take yourself up there.

29:09.828 --> 29:13.163
As a matter of fact,
we both should go up there.

29:13.264 --> 29:14.565
I mean, we kinda owe ourselves

29:14.666 --> 29:16.967
one of our famous fishing expeditions.

29:17.068 --> 29:19.003
Maybe make some music
together like we used to,

29:19.104 --> 29:20.371
you wanna do it?

29:20.472 --> 29:22.573
Come on, how many songs
did we write in that cabin?

29:22.674 --> 29:24.508
Oh my God.

29:24.609 --> 29:26.877
Some of them were God-awful too,
weren't they?

29:26.978 --> 29:28.779
(CHUCKLES) That is true.

29:28.880 --> 29:30.547
(LAUGHS)

29:30.649 --> 29:31.749
I agree with you, Will.

29:31.850 --> 29:34.385
A fishing trip is due, let's set a date.

29:34.486 --> 29:37.254
That's right, I got a social calendar,
I'm gonna fit you in.

29:37.355 --> 29:39.189
(BOTH LAUGH)

29:39.290 --> 29:40.557
Yeah.

29:43.561 --> 29:45.462
AMY: What if I can't get
the stallion to accept

29:45.563 --> 29:47.464
the mare and her baby?

29:47.565 --> 29:49.033
I don't even wanna think about that,

29:49.134 --> 29:50.734
I can't just turn them out in the wild,

29:50.835 --> 29:53.604
they'd be such easy prey.

29:53.705 --> 29:55.372
You'll do it.

29:55.473 --> 29:57.908
I've seen you with that stallion before.

29:59.344 --> 30:01.945
Was that four years ago,
during the cull?

30:02.047 --> 30:03.547
Yeah.

30:04.549 --> 30:06.684
You saved him and his herd.

30:07.686 --> 30:09.653
I think he'll remember you.

30:11.222 --> 30:13.590
I remember something about that time,
too.

30:15.460 --> 30:17.127
You proposed.

30:17.228 --> 30:19.129
Again.

30:19.230 --> 30:20.864
- Yes, I did.
- (LAUGHS)

30:21.933 --> 30:24.234
And now we're married.

30:24.335 --> 30:26.570
We have a beautiful baby girl.

30:26.671 --> 30:29.740
We're starting our
own business together.

30:29.841 --> 30:32.576
I'd say we're doing pretty good.

30:32.677 --> 30:35.446
Yeah. Yeah, we are.

30:35.547 --> 30:37.581
Yeah.

30:37.682 --> 30:39.516
You know what?

30:39.617 --> 30:41.618
This is all gonna work.

30:42.620 --> 30:44.822
Because you're the miracle girl.

30:44.923 --> 30:47.491
(BOTH LAUGH)

