31:10.831 --> 31:12.231
(HOOVES STOMP)

31:13.367 --> 31:14.901
- Are you okay with this?
- Mhmm.

31:15.002 --> 31:17.570
- All right.
- AMY: Okay, let him out.

31:17.671 --> 31:19.272
(STALLION WHINNIES)

31:19.373 --> 31:21.240
(HOOVES THUNDER)

31:22.509 --> 31:24.577
(LOUD WHINNIES)

31:25.879 --> 31:27.213
(HOOVES THUD)

31:27.314 --> 31:29.415
- JACK: Amy!
- Whoa!

31:29.516 --> 31:31.584
(AGITATED WHINNIES)

31:32.453 --> 31:35.188
I need you to do something for me.

31:35.289 --> 31:36.990
To help me.

31:38.259 --> 31:40.460
- You see them?
- (SNORTING)

31:41.595 --> 31:43.663
They don't have a home.

31:45.132 --> 31:46.766
(STALLION BLOWS SOFTLY)

31:46.867 --> 31:49.269
And you can give them one, okay?

31:50.671 --> 31:51.905
(STALLION SNORTS)

31:52.006 --> 31:53.855
Please?

32:02.149 --> 32:04.717
(STALLION NICKERS) There you go.

32:10.157 --> 32:11.558
Go on now.

32:11.659 --> 32:14.260
You be nice to them.

32:15.296 --> 32:17.030
(HOOVES CLOMP)

32:22.770 --> 32:24.838
(JACK SIGHS)

32:27.575 --> 32:29.142
We did it.

32:30.277 --> 32:31.611
(JACK CHUCKLES)

32:31.712 --> 32:33.179
Thanks for all your help, Will.

32:33.280 --> 32:34.614
My pleasure, always.

32:34.715 --> 32:36.616
And thank you for taking
on two more mouths to feed.

32:36.717 --> 32:38.385
Well, like I always say,

32:38.486 --> 32:40.353
to them, I'm just the guy with the food.

32:40.454 --> 32:42.489
(ALL LAUGH) See ya.

32:42.590 --> 32:44.491
- You take care.
- I will.

32:44.592 --> 32:45.392
- Okay.
- Thank you.

32:45.493 --> 32:47.494
- See ya.
- See ya later.

32:48.696 --> 32:49.829
- Drive careful.
- Yep!

32:49.930 --> 32:51.898
Oh, I guess it's my turn

32:51.999 --> 32:54.200
to say thank you for the advice.

32:54.301 --> 32:56.636
That's right, the shoe is on
the other foot for a change,

32:56.737 --> 32:59.439
it's kinda nice, isn't it?

32:59.540 --> 33:00.874
I'll see you at the fishing cabin.

33:00.975 --> 33:02.742
Yep, it's on my social calendar.

33:02.843 --> 33:04.310
I'm definitely gonna see you there.

33:04.412 --> 33:06.246
Oh, hang on a second. Oh, I totally...

33:06.347 --> 33:09.416
here it is, I come up...
I've been working on something.

33:09.517 --> 33:10.784
Okay, it's a song.

33:10.885 --> 33:12.986
It's my ex's birthday coming up,

33:13.087 --> 33:14.954
and I'm okay,
I think the lyrics are pretty good,

33:15.056 --> 33:16.523
but I'm stuck a on the hook.

33:16.624 --> 33:18.425
I wonder if you could
just take a look at it,

33:18.526 --> 33:19.793
and make it good?

33:19.894 --> 33:21.895
- I mean, you're the music guy.
- Oh, no, I'm not.

33:21.996 --> 33:25.265
You definitely are. Please help me.

33:25.366 --> 33:28.301
You know,
I think this new "romantic Will"

33:28.402 --> 33:30.103
has lost his mind,

33:30.204 --> 33:32.072
but sure, I'll have a look at it.

33:32.173 --> 33:33.606
- Thank you, buddy.
- It's good to see you.

33:33.707 --> 33:35.809
It's always good to see you.

33:35.910 --> 33:38.344
(BOTH LAUGH)

33:40.047 --> 33:41.247
See ya, Jack.

33:41.348 --> 33:43.550
(TRUCKS RUMBLE)

33:47.655 --> 33:50.156
(TRUCK SHUTS OFF, KEYS JINGLE)

33:50.257 --> 33:52.158
Hey, you know, now's not the best time,

33:52.259 --> 33:54.894
Georgie has this important thing, so...

33:54.995 --> 33:56.696
Just stop, all right? We need to talk.

33:56.797 --> 33:58.298
- KIM: Head up. Head up.
- Okay.

33:58.399 --> 34:00.166
I don't know how to act
around you right now,

34:00.267 --> 34:01.468
you just, you're being weird.

34:01.569 --> 34:03.369
I am not being weird, and you're the one

34:03.471 --> 34:06.239
walking around me like
you're on eggshells.

34:06.340 --> 34:08.308
I'm fine. I was a little taken aback,

34:08.409 --> 34:10.110
you know, this whole dating thing

34:10.210 --> 34:11.643
just kinda caught me
off guard a little bit,

34:11.745 --> 34:13.813
but I'm... I'm fine.

34:14.882 --> 34:16.282
- You're really okay?
- Yeah.

34:16.382 --> 34:18.118
Because if you can't
handle being friends,

34:18.219 --> 34:19.385
I-I don't know how this...

34:19.487 --> 34:21.521
Can't handle being your friend?!

34:21.621 --> 34:24.324
Don't be ridiculous,
of course I can handle it.

34:24.425 --> 34:25.859
I mean, to tell you the truth,

34:25.960 --> 34:27.627
I'm dating too, okay?

34:27.728 --> 34:31.164
If you wanna know,
I'm dating a lot, actually.

34:31.264 --> 34:34.266
So, the truth is,
we were never really cut out

34:34.368 --> 34:36.034
as boyfriends and girlfriends go,
anyway.

34:36.137 --> 34:37.971
I mean, look how many times
we tried to make that work.

34:38.072 --> 34:41.074
That-that is what's ridiculous, so.

34:41.175 --> 34:43.076
I think we dodged a bullet there.

34:43.177 --> 34:44.744
And we are just way
better off being friends,

34:44.844 --> 34:46.746
so that's what we should be, friends.

34:46.847 --> 34:49.516
Great, well, I guess we're just friends!

34:49.617 --> 34:51.284
Great.

34:56.190 --> 34:58.391
So what is so important with Georgie,
I mean...

34:58.492 --> 34:59.926
Kim Price.

35:00.027 --> 35:02.095
She is very big in the
show jumping world,

35:02.196 --> 35:04.797
and Georgie has a huge opportunity

35:04.899 --> 35:07.033
to be coached by her,

35:07.134 --> 35:09.669
so she has this audition thing.

35:09.770 --> 35:12.972
And we're total nervous wrecks,
if you wanna know.

35:14.942 --> 35:17.877
Sounds like she could use
another fan in her corner.

35:19.446 --> 35:21.214
Yeah, I bet she could.

35:21.315 --> 35:23.049
<i>KIM: Okay, Georgie, are you ready?</i>

35:23.150 --> 35:24.851
<i>I'm gonna time this!</i>

35:28.689 --> 35:29.722
We've got this!

35:29.823 --> 35:31.457
Let's go!

35:31.559 --> 35:32.892
Come on!

35:33.961 --> 35:35.461
Come on, honey.

35:37.698 --> 35:39.632
(PHOENIX SNORTS)

35:45.239 --> 35:47.607
(HOOVES THUD)

35:47.708 --> 35:49.509
(TACK JINGLES)

35:51.679 --> 35:53.046
(PHOENIX SNORTS)

35:59.920 --> 36:01.754
(PHOENIX PANTS)

36:03.857 --> 36:06.359
Atta girl!

36:07.528 --> 36:09.395
(PHOENIX SNORTS)

36:11.298 --> 36:13.499
(PHOENIX PANTS)

36:14.802 --> 36:17.136
Good! Excellent!

36:17.238 --> 36:18.771
I did it? Really?

36:18.872 --> 36:20.840
Okay, well,
you may have been a second over my time,

36:20.941 --> 36:22.942
but I'm sure not going
to be picky about that.

36:23.043 --> 36:26.079
I would be proud to
coach the two of you.

36:26.180 --> 36:28.715
Good boy, Phoenix!

36:28.816 --> 36:30.617
(LAUGHS) Thank you!

36:30.718 --> 36:32.452
(LOU AND MITCH CHEER)

36:32.553 --> 36:34.520
She did it! Oh!

36:36.824 --> 36:39.259
(CLAPS) Woo! Good job, honey!

36:40.894 --> 36:44.154
(LAUGHS) Good boy!

36:48.175 --> 36:49.676
<i>(BIRDS CHIRP)</i>

36:49.777 --> 36:51.678
AMY: It was a little touch
and go there for a while,

36:51.779 --> 36:53.880
but finally the mare and foal
were accepted into the herd.

36:53.981 --> 36:57.083
Thanks to Grandpa and Will,
and my wonderful husband.

36:57.184 --> 36:59.018
I knew that you guys
would be successful.

36:59.120 --> 37:01.721
And I'm-and I'm really proud
of the way the two of you

37:01.822 --> 37:03.390
are putting your business together.

37:03.491 --> 37:05.592
- Well, thanks, Lisa.
- And in keeping with that,

37:05.693 --> 37:07.961
I would like to be one of
your first full-time clients.

37:08.062 --> 37:09.262
What?

37:09.363 --> 37:11.264
I've decided to turn
all Fairfield vet duties

37:11.365 --> 37:13.266
over to the new partnership.

37:14.802 --> 37:16.703
- That's amazing!
- Thank you!

37:16.804 --> 37:18.071
My pleasure.

37:19.173 --> 37:21.307
Georgie had a big triumph today too.

37:21.409 --> 37:22.976
She totally won Kim over.

37:23.077 --> 37:24.944
<i>Ty: Hmm, that's great!</i>

37:30.351 --> 37:31.985
I thought what you did
for Amy and Ty tonight

37:32.086 --> 37:34.587
was very thoughtful.

37:34.688 --> 37:36.623
Oh, well yes, of course.

37:36.724 --> 37:38.958
I'd rather keep it in the family.

37:39.059 --> 37:41.995
Because family is very important to me.

37:42.096 --> 37:45.231
I've been a bit of an ass,
and I'm sorry.

37:46.734 --> 37:49.102
I know what a loyal person you can be,

37:49.203 --> 37:51.438
especially when it comes to family.

37:51.539 --> 37:53.773
And I want you to know, I do understand

37:53.874 --> 37:57.210
why you need to be with Evelyn,
and I support you.

37:58.412 --> 38:00.547
Okay.

38:00.648 --> 38:03.650
Good, 'cause I,
I booked my ticket already.

38:03.751 --> 38:05.985
(LAUGHS) Of course you did.

38:07.121 --> 38:08.655
I wouldn't expect anything less

38:08.756 --> 38:10.490
from my strong, independent wife,

38:10.591 --> 38:13.059
who I'm going to miss very much.

38:14.428 --> 38:18.331
Well, haven't you come a
long way this week, cowboy.

38:22.069 --> 38:24.771
(CRICKETS CHIRP)

38:27.908 --> 38:29.008
(HORSES SNORT)

38:31.212 --> 38:33.480
- Hey.
- Hey.

38:33.581 --> 38:37.844
Look, I'm really sorry about Kim.

38:38.652 --> 38:41.054
Maybe it was a really dumb thing to do.

38:41.155 --> 38:43.490
No, don't think like that.

38:43.591 --> 38:47.360
Honestly, Georgie,
you're so advanced now,

38:47.461 --> 38:48.928
maybe you do need someone like Kim

38:49.029 --> 38:51.197
to take you to the next level.

38:51.298 --> 38:54.033
- Are you sure?
- I'm sure.

38:55.503 --> 38:57.470
But don't think that I'm
not gonna keep watching you

38:57.571 --> 39:01.040
like a hawk.
I'll never stop being there for you.

39:07.515 --> 39:10.717
(SIGHS) Are you sure I can't
just drive you to the airport?

39:10.818 --> 39:12.685
No honey, I just,
I prefer to drive myself,

39:12.786 --> 39:15.288
and park the car there, and I hate...

39:15.389 --> 39:17.624
I hate airport goodbyes.

39:19.056 --> 39:20.685
(SIGHS) I'm gonna miss you.

39:20.995 --> 39:23.663
I'm sorry to leave. I'll be fine.

39:24.698 --> 39:26.866
Give my best to Aunt Evelyn.

39:26.967 --> 39:29.402
- I mean that!
- I will, I will.

39:30.471 --> 39:34.741
But most important,
you take care of yourself.

39:35.383 --> 39:37.977
Because I won't be there to
help you fend off all the boys.

39:38.078 --> 39:40.947
Oh, the boys. Mhmm. Okay.

39:44.718 --> 39:46.753
I gotta go.

39:46.854 --> 39:48.354
(CLEARS HER THROAT)

39:50.824 --> 39:52.892
(EXHALES)

39:52.993 --> 39:55.428
(SIGHS)

39:58.632 --> 40:00.433
I love you.

40:06.640 --> 40:08.107
I love you more.

40:13.414 --> 40:15.915
Don't have any fun without me.

40:16.016 --> 40:17.784
(LAUGHS)

40:19.453 --> 40:21.321
(BIRDS CHIRP)

40:21.422 --> 40:23.856
(PLAYS A TUNE ON THE GUITAR)

40:27.661 --> 40:30.563
♪ Now I can say I love you ♪

40:30.664 --> 40:32.999
♪ And mean it even more ♪

40:33.100 --> 40:35.168
♪ A second chance, a second dance ♪

40:35.269 --> 40:38.237
♪ More precious than before ♪

40:38.339 --> 40:40.573
♪ If your love is broken ♪

40:40.674 --> 40:43.142
♪ And it leaves you on your own ♪

40:43.243 --> 40:47.046
♪ Trust that time will come and go ♪

40:47.147 --> 40:49.983
♪ And your heart
will lead you home ♪

40:50.084 --> 40:52.151
(PLAYS A RIFF)

40:55.356 --> 40:57.156
(STOPS PLAYING)

40:58.626 --> 40:59.792
TIM: What's that?

40:59.893 --> 41:02.362
It's nothing,
it's a song that Will wrote,

41:02.463 --> 41:05.198
I'm just helpin' him out, is all.

41:05.299 --> 41:08.368
Wow, a love song?
Kinda bad timing for that.

41:08.469 --> 41:11.070
With Lisa gettin' out of dodge, right?

41:11.171 --> 41:12.939
Are you still here?

41:13.040 --> 41:15.408
I was kinda hoping you'd be gone by now.

41:15.509 --> 41:17.076
Relax, Jack.

41:18.512 --> 41:20.146
It's temporary.

41:21.181 --> 41:23.816
You know what, I need a drink.

41:32.793 --> 41:36.162
♪ There comes a day when
we look beyond this ♪

41:36.263 --> 41:39.532
♪ Past the dreams
that arose from dust ♪

41:39.633 --> 41:43.042
♪ How they caught like wildfire ♪

41:43.203 --> 41:45.204
♪ How they still got a hold on me ♪

41:45.305 --> 41:47.540
- Hey.
- Hey.

41:50.878 --> 41:53.980
I-I honestly did not know about Mitch.

41:55.516 --> 41:57.116
But I warned you.

41:57.217 --> 41:59.318
Not to go down that road, I know.

42:00.454 --> 42:02.689
I know.

42:02.790 --> 42:05.591
Sometimes the head'll take
that good advice, right?

42:05.693 --> 42:07.994
But the heart...

42:08.095 --> 42:11.364
Well, you kept your promise, so...
I guess...

42:11.465 --> 42:13.633
I guess I owe you the truth.

42:14.802 --> 42:18.594
About what happened with Casey and me.

42:22.176 --> 42:25.253
I drove down to that
rodeo she was putting on,

42:25.579 --> 42:28.056
and it gave me a lot of time to think.

42:28.482 --> 42:30.798
Maybe too much time.

42:34.388 --> 42:38.116
You know, I pretty much decided that...

42:38.258 --> 42:40.259
♪ Remember why ♪

42:41.261 --> 42:44.230
Time is a funny thing.

42:46.467 --> 42:48.167
(HORSES WHINNY)

42:50.871 --> 42:52.872
(HOOVES THUNDER)

42:55.075 --> 42:56.609
(LOUD WHINNIES)

